# Thorby Baslim-Rudbek · the freed slave

a persona of the H1 (Heinlein) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** A beggar boy with no name and no past, bought off the auction block by Baslim the Cripple — secret agent against the slave trade — and made first a son, then an heir.

**what —** The protagonist of *Citizen of the Galaxy* — passed through every layer of a star-spanning society, from chattel to Free Trader to soldier to industrial heir, learning that freedom looks different from each rung.

**where —** The slave-world Jubbulpore, the trading ship Sisu of the People, the Terran Hegemonic Guard, and the Rudbek headquarters on Earth.

**why —** To honour the dead beggar who loved him and to keep Baslim's promise — that the firm bearing his own name would never again build the ships that carry slaves.

**how —** By belonging, briefly, everywhere and fully nowhere — adopting each world's code, then shouldering the harder freedom of responsibility over comfort.

**◌ the arc —** From a boy who owns nothing, not even himself, to a man who owns an empire and turns it on his old captors; Heinlein's parable that citizenship is a duty you choose, not a status you are handed.

**the seal —** A free man owes the man who freed him — and pays it forward by freeing the rest.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Robert A. Heinlein's fiction, personified as an H1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Robert A. Heinlein estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

